Area D — Data & Session Bugs
Issue #5: Console Error in getCartItems
Problem Description
A console error appears on certain pages originating from a getCartItems function. The error likely results from a failed database query — possibly a missing join, a deleted relation, or a malformed query condition.
Investigation Steps
•	Locate getCartItems in the codebase — note the full query including joins and conditions
•	Check what relationships are joined (e.g., cart_items joined to products) — verify those foreign keys exist and are consistent
•	Test the query directly in the database client to reproduce the error
•	Check if the error occurs when the cart is empty, when a user is not logged in, or when a product has been deleted but the cart item remains
Fix Instructions
•	Add proper null-safety and error boundaries around the cart query
•	If a product is deleted, either cascade-delete cart items or handle orphaned items gracefully
•	Wrap the error with a user-friendly fallback (empty cart state) rather than letting it propagate to console
•	Remove debug console.error calls or replace them with proper error tracking

Issue #6: Wishlist Shows Random Default Items
Problem Description
The wishlist page displays placeholder or default items instead of the actual products added by the user. This indicates either placeholder data is hardcoded in the UI, or the wishlist query is not fetching user-specific records.
Investigation Steps
•	Inspect the wishlist component — look for any hardcoded mock data arrays or placeholder product lists
•	Locate the wishlist data fetching function — confirm it filters by the current authenticated user ID
•	Check the wishlist database table — does it have a user_id foreign key that is being applied in the query?
•	Inspect the relationship between wishlist items and products — ensure product details are joined correctly
•	Check if the wishlist hook/context initializes with mock data before the real fetch completes
Fix Instructions
•	Remove all hardcoded placeholder/mock data from the wishlist component and its data providers
•	Ensure the wishlist query always filters by WHERE user_id = auth.user.id
•	Show a proper loading state while fetch is in progress, and an empty state if no items are found
•	Test with multiple users to confirm data isolation


 
