Issue #13: Lookbook Modification — Fork Architecture
Design Principle
Users should be able to modify existing lookbooks without altering the original. This is a 'fork' pattern — creating a personal copy when edits are made.
Proposed Architecture
•	When a user clicks 'Modify' on any lookbook (their own or another user's), do not open the original for editing
•	Instead, silently create a copy: INSERT INTO lookbooks ... (original_lookbook_id = original.id, is_copy = true, user_id = current_user.id)
•	Copy all lookbook_products records for the new lookbook ID
•	Open the creation flow in 'Edit Mode' pre-populated with the copied data
•	Save the copy to the user's profile under 'My Lookbooks'
•	Display a notice: 'This is your personal copy of [Original Name] by [Creator]' with a link back to the original
•	The is_copy and original_lookbook_id fields enable attribution and discovery linking


 
